Here is a concise report of what exists under `/Users/duhl/git/ui/apps/org-next/src` for `createServerFn` + auth/login behavior.

## Summary

There are **six files** that use `createServerFn`. Auth-related behavior appears in **five** of them; **`src/routes/_authed/-tenants.ts`** only posts to the org API and does **not** implement session checks or `/login` redirects in the handler (auth is implicit via `postOrgApiJson` / token resolution in `org-api.server.ts`).

There are **no** files named `middleware` and **no** `middleware` string matches under `src/`.

---

### 1. `src/server/app-bootstrap.ts`

**Imports:** `redirect` from `@tanstack/react-router`; `createServerFn` from `@tanstack/react-start`; `getOrgApiJson` from `./org-api.server`; `OrgApiError` from `./error`.

**Pattern:** Three server functions. `fetchCurrentUser` loads `/users/me` (treats 404 as unauthenticated). `fetchTenants` loads `/tenants` (401 propagates). `fetchAppBootstrapData` returns `null` if `user === null`. **`getAppBootstrapData`** redirects to `/login` when bootstrap is missing or on `OrgApiError` with status **401**.

```7:78:/Users/duhl/git/ui/apps/org-next/src/server/app-bootstrap.ts
const fetchCurrentUser = createServerFn({ method: "GET" }).handler(
  async (): Promise<User | null> => {
    try {
      return await getOrgApiJson<User>("/users/me");
    } catch (error) {
      if (error instanceof OrgApiError && error.status === 404) {
        return null;
      }

      throw error;
    }
  },
);

const fetchTenants = createServerFn({ method: "GET" }).handler(
  async (): Promise<Tenant[]> => {
    try {
      return await getOrgApiJson<Tenant[]>("/tenants");
    } catch (error) {
      if (error instanceof OrgApiError && error.status === 401) {
        throw error;
      }

      return [];
    }
  },
);

// ... fetchAppBootstrapData combines user + tenants ...

export const getAppBootstrapData = createServerFn({ method: "GET" }).handler(
  async (): Promise<AppBootstrap> => {
    try {
      const appBootstrap = await fetchAppBootstrapData();

      if (!appBootstrap) {
        throw redirect({ to: "/login" });
      }

      return appBootstrap;
    } catch (error) {
      if (error instanceof OrgApiError && error.status === 401) {
        throw redirect({ to: "/login" });
      }

      throw error;
    }
  },
);
```

