## Auth utilities actually used inside these `createServerFn` handlers

| Utility / import | Where |
|------------------|--------|
| `getAppBootstrapData` (wraps user + tenants via org API) | `_authed/index.tsx`, `-campaigns.ts`, and defined in `app-bootstrap.ts` |
| `getOrgApiJson` | `app-bootstrap.ts` |
| `useAuthTokenSession` | `_login/auth.ts` only (direct session read) |
| `redirect` from `@tanstack/react-router` | `app-bootstrap.ts`, `_authed/index.tsx`, `-campaigns.ts`, `_login/auth.ts` |
| `OrgApiError` + status **401** â†’ `/login` | `app-bootstrap.ts`, `_authed/index.tsx`, `-campaigns.ts` |

There are **no** `getSession`, `getUser`, or `getAuth` symbol names in `src/`; the closest equivalents are **`fetchCurrentUser`** (GET `/users/me`), **`getAppBootstrapData`**, and **`useAuthTokenSession`**.

